commit.message: Bump version to 2.22

protocol-smtp: Fix pre-standard address parsing

SMTP commands of the form "MAIL FROM:address" or "MAIL FROM address"
(lacking the angle braces around the address) failed to parse as a
result of commit 8a36f4ce. This restores the original behavior.
tests: Fix up the starttls tests for the new TLS handshake details

starttls-gnutls: Enhance TLS handshake details logging

Output the key exchange and cipher algorithms in addition to the
protocol and MAC algorithm.

Also drop the certificate type, as it is hard coded to be X.509 and so
cannot be anything different.
Bump version to 2.21

starttls-gnutls: Make the "compatibility mode" optional

The compatibility mode setting was unconditionally enabled when setting
up TLS. This makes it optional.

starttls-gnutls: Avoid building a priority cache

Use gnutls_priority_set_direct to avoid the extra step of building a
priority cache, as we only use it once.

starttls-gnutls: Removed call to request client certificate

Nothing in our code actually uses the client certificate, so this is
just extraneous. Most clients won't provide a certificate anyways.

starttls-gnutls: Fix crash bug in handling of DH parameter loading

The DH parameter data is only stored as a pointer, and so must NOT be
deinitialized before they are used. This would cause random segfaults.
starttls-gnutls.c: Output handshake failure before deinit
Bump version to 2.20
Updated README and added an INSTALL document
Merge branch 'starttls'

starttls-gnutls: Load DH params from a file instead of generating

Generating DH parameters on each connection is expensive, especially if
anything more than the lowest allowed security level (1024 bits) is
desired. Allow the parameters to be loaded from a file instead of being
generated on each connection.
tests: Reorganized the STARTTLS tests
starttls-gnutls: Moved some global static variables local

starttls-gnutls: Load the required files on startup

This causes any configuration errors to be noticed on startup instead of
blowing up mailfront when the STARTTLS command is issued.
starttls-gnutls: Tweaked a couple of messages
protocol-smtp: Move STARTTLS plugin into the protocol directly
tests: Rename protocol related tests, drop "front" suffix
protocol-smtp: Rework documentation to separate features and configuration
Add a way of configuring the TLS implementation
plugin-starttls-gnutls: Move most of the implementation to separate source
plugin-starttls-gnutls: Added notes to NEWS and TODO
plugin-starttls-gnutls: Add documentation page
plugin-starttls-gnutls: Attempt SMTPS mode only if a certificate is set
plugin-starttls-gnutls: Tweak C style differences
plugin-starttls-gnutls: New plugin for native STARTTLS support
plugin-starttls-ucspi: Add missing link to documentation
plugin-api: Add a note about the RESPONSE_FINAL bit in the docs
